<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Instruction Brochure - Client Dashboard</title>
    <script src="https://cdn.tailwindcss.com"></script>
</head>

<body class="bg-zinc-900">

    <!-- Header -->
    <header class="bg-gray-800 text-white py-4 text-center">
        <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold">Client Dashboard - How It Works</h1>
    </header>

    <!-- Section -->
    <section class="bg-zinc-800 max-w-4xl mx-auto mt-8 p-6 rounded-lg shadow-lg">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">1. Getting Started as a Client</h2>
        <p class="text-white mb-4">To start using the client dashboard, follow these steps:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-white">
            <li>Sign up as a client or log in if you already have an account.</li>
            <li>Complete your profile by filling in the required information.</li>
            <li>Access the dashboard to create and manage your projects.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mt-8 mb-4">2. Creating a Project</h2>
        <p class="text-white mb-4">Clients can easily create projects by following these steps:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-white">
            <li>Click on the "Create Project" button from the dashboard.</li>
            <li>Provide the project title, description, required skills, budget, and deadline.</li>
            <li>Submit the project to make it visible to freelancers.</li>
            <li>Manage posted projects and view freelancer bids.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mt-8 mb-4">3. Managing Notifications</h2>
        <p class="text-white mb-4">Clients can view important notifications in the dashboard:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-white">
            <li>Get real-time updates when freelancers apply for your project.</li>
            <li>Receive notifications when a freelancer submits their work.</li>
            <li>Track the progress of your projects through status updates.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mt-8 mb-4">4. Reviewing Freelancers</h2>
        <p class="text-white mb-4">After the completion of a project, you can:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-white">
            <li>Review the work submitted by freelancers.</li>
            <li>Rate freelancers based on the quality of work and professionalism.</li>
            <li>Provide feedback to help other clients in the future.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mt-8 mb-4">5. Managing Your Projects</h2>
        <p class="text-white mb-4">The dashboard allows clients to manage ongoing and completed projects:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-white">
            <li>View all posted projects and monitor freelancer bids.</li>
            <li>Close projects once completed and mark them as finished.</li>
            <li>Communicate with freelancers via the messaging system to clarify requirements.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mt-8 mb-4">6. Making Payments</h2>
        <p class="text-white">You can securely pay freelancers after reviewing and approving their work:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-white">
            <li>Use the integrated payment gateway for secure transactions.</li>
            <li>Track all payments made through the "Payments" tab in the dashboard.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- Footer -->
    <footer class="bg-gray-800 text-white text-center py-4 mt-8">
        <p>&copy; 2024 Freelancer's Hub. All Rights Reserved.</p>
    </footer>

</body>

</html>
